  <entry>
    <title>Feature #27 (New): Engineering file management features</title>
    <link rel="alternate" href="http://opendesignengine.net/issues/27"/>
    <id>http://opendesignengine.net/issues/27</id>
    <updated>2011-04-09T16:17:47+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>J. Simmons</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;Source code control for embedded systems or computer based controls, etc should be stored in one of the available Version Control Systems (VCS) such as SVN, bzr, git, etc.  But engineering documents offer challenges that VCS do not handle well (very large, on order of GB files, primarily binary files).  Here are some specific requirements for engineering documents.  (Should investigate Enterprise CMS like &lt;a href="http://www.alfresco.com/products/dm/" class="external"&gt;Alfresco&lt;/a&gt; for underlying capabilities, as many of the features below are available in this class of tools.)&lt;/p&gt;    </content>
  </entry>
